    "body": "nvim seeks for config and data in `/home/root` instead of `/root`",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I guess this depends on what `$HOME` is set to. `/home/root` is probably just a guess that Nvim makes if `$HOME` isn't set, or maybe it's the result of `uv_os_homedir`.\n\nHow are you starting nvim, are you doing `sudo nvim` or are you running as root already in a shell? And what is `$HOME` in that shell? And what is `:echo $HOME` from Nvim?\n\nThese sure look related:\n\n- https://snapcraft.io/docs/home-outside-home\n- https://askubuntu.com/q/1207472",
